        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 4:12PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 412 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Calhan, or 28 miles east of Colorado Springs, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Calhan and Ramah.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
